Azure Load Balancer distributes incoming traffic across multiple resources to ensure high availability and reliability.

It supports:

* Public load balancing (internet-facing)
* Internal load balancing (within VNet)

For example, a web application can distribute user requests across multiple VMs.

A real-life use case is an e-commerce website handling thousands of users simultaneously.

Another example is ensuring application availability during server failures.

Load balancing improves performance and fault tolerance.
